cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use tokenfit in your research, please cite it using this metadata."
title: "tokenfit: heuristic token-count estimation for LLM context windows"
version: 0.2.0
date-released: 2024-01-01
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/vdeshmukh203/tokenfit"
url: "https://github.com/vdeshmukh203/tokenfit"
abstract: >
  tokenfit is a pure-Python, zero-dependency library for estimating the
  number of tokens a text or chat-message list will consume when sent to
  a large language model (LLM). It uses calibrated character-to-token
  ratios for OpenAI GPT, Anthropic Claude, and Google Gemini model
  families, returning conservative (rounded-up) estimates without making
  any API calls or loading a tokenizer library. The package is suitable
  for pre-flight context-window budget checks, prompt-routing logic, and
  interactive tooling.
authors:
  - family-names: Deshmukh
    given-names: Vaibhav
    orcid: ""
keywords:
  - large language models
  - tokenization
  - token estimation
  - context window
  - GPT
  - Claude
  - Gemini
  - natural language processing
